The '''Bratach Gorm''' (a.k.a. Blue Banner) is the highest prize given by the [[Scottish Piping Society of London]] and was introduced in 1938. It can only be won by those who have won the; Highland Society of London Gold Medal at the [[Argyllshire Gathering]] or [[Northern Meeting]] or the first prize at the [[William Gillies Memorial Cup]].<ref>{{cite news | last = Nicol | first = Angus | title = London piping society prizes | newspaper = The Times | location = London | pages = 54 | date = February 6, 2006 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | last = Nicol | first = Angus | title = Scottish Piping Society of London returns to Glazier's Hall in fine form | newspaper = The Times | location = London | pages = 44 | date = December 29, 2004 }}</ref> The monetary value as a primary [[Pibroch]] is £500.<ref>{{cite news | last = Nicol | first = Angus | title = London pipers play for finer prizes | newspaper = The Times | location = London | pages = 33 | date = November 5, 2003 }}</ref> In 1994 the competition pool was further reduced in protest at the selection of judges.<ref>{{cite news | last = Nicol | first = Angus | title = Youngsters keep the piping hot | newspaper = The Times | location = London | date = December 6, 1994 }}</ref> In order to win the annual [[London Piping Championship]] an entrant must have won this and another award.<ref>{{cite news | last = Nicol | first = Angus | title = Little to lament as the Scots come to London | newspaper = The Times | location = London | date = December 28, 1992 }}</ref>
