{{Infobox song contest | name = Melodifestivalen | year = 1981 | theme = | logo = | final = 21 February 1981 | presenters = [[Janne Loffe Carlsson]] | winner = "[[Fångad i en dröm]]" by [[Björn Skifs]] | vote = Regional juries | host = | venue = [[Cirkus (Stockholm)|Cirkus]], [[Stockholm]] | entries = | interval = | opening = }}
'''[[Melodifestivalen]] 1981''' was the selection for the 21st song to represent [[Sweden]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest]]. It was the 20th time that this system of picking a song had been used. 90 songs were submitted to [[Sveriges Television|SVT]] for the competition. The final was broadcast on [[SVT1|TV1]] but was not broadcast on radio. It was the second time that [[Lasse Holm]] and [[Kikki Danielsson]] had been beaten into second place by Björn Skifs, after [[Melodifestivalen 1978|1978]].
