{{Unreferenced|date=March 2010}} {{Infobox beauty pageant | winner = [[Sharlene Wells Hawkes]] | represented = {{flagicon|Utah}} [[Miss Utah|Utah]] | date = September 8, 1984 | presenters = [[Gary Collins (actor)|Gary Collins]] | venue = [[Boardwalk Hall]], [[Atlantic City]], [[New Jersey]] | broadcaster = [[NBC]] | before = [[Miss America 1984|1984]] | next = [[Miss America 1986|1986]] }}
'''Miss America 1985''', the 58th [[Miss America]] pageant, was broadcast from the [[Boardwalk Hall]] in [[Atlantic City, New Jersey]], on September 8, 1984 on [[NBC|NBC Network]].
The winner, [[Paraguay]] native [[Sharlene Wells]], became the first foreign-born Miss America. She later became a horse-racing and football commentator for [[ESPN]].
Another of the five finalists, [[Lauren Green]], is currently a correspondent on the [[Fox News Channel]].
