The '''Norwegian Military Tattoo''' (''Norsk Militær Tattoo'') is a military festival held biannually in the Norwegian capital of [[Oslo]]. The first tattoo was held in 1994 in [[Hamar]], which is north of [[Oslo]]. The tattoo has been held in the [[Oslo Spektrum]] since 1996.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oslo.com/event/norwegian-military-tattoo/|title=Norwegian Military Tattoo|website=oslo.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oslospektrum.no/norwegian-military-tattoo.4971183-133570.html|title=Norwegian Military Tattoo|website=Oslo Spektrum Arena}}</ref> It features military bands and drill teams of the [[Norwegian Armed Forces]] (such as the band and honour guard of [[Hans Majestet Kongens Garde]]) as well as the bands and drill teams of foreign countries.
With over 800 participants on stage, the Norwegian Military Tattoo is Norway's largest indoor show. The tattoo's official TV partner is [[NRK1]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://forsvaret.no/en/facts/culture/norwegian-military-tattoo|title=Norwegian Military Tattoo|website=Norwegian Armed Forces}}</ref>
